annotationA: Gamma-aminobutyric acid transaminase, isoform A; Pyridoxal phosphate binding; 4-aminobutyrate transaminase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular amino acid metabolic process; gamma-aminobutyric acid metabolic process; Belongs to the class-III pyridoxal-phosphate-dependent aminotransferase family
annotationB: Aldehyde dehydrogenase type III (Aldh-III) confers a xenobiotic stress resistance by oxidising aromatic aldehydes (benzaldehyde). It also neutralises the lipid aldehydes formed after the attack of reactive oxygen and radicals, such as malondialdehyde during lipid peroxidation. The catalytic redox reaction uses NAD(P)+ as a cofactor
